<paragraph blockId="24.[136,1452,158,617]" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,241,194,220]" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">Notes:—</emphasis>
This species is morphologically similar to 
<emphasis box="[720,1041,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer ex Rojas-Alvarado &amp; Karremans" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Ames" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[720,833,195,220]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cereus">M. cereus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Lindl." baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[845,1041,194,220]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="octomerioides">M. octomerioides</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1992" baseAuthorityName="Barb. Rodr." baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[1097,1252,194,220]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulvinatus">
<emphasis box="[1097,1252,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">M. pulvinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. From 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer ex Rojas-Alvarado &amp; Karremans" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Ames" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[1334,1444,195,220]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cereus">
<emphasis box="[1334,1444,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">M. cereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Soto Arenas" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="A. Rich. &amp; Galeotti" box="[136,283,231,256]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="congestus">
<emphasis box="[136,283,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">M. congestus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by the narrow elliptic leaves 
<emphasis box="[796,819,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">vs</emphasis>
. broad elliptic to ovate, ovate petals 
<emphasis box="[1231,1254,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">vs</emphasis>
. oblong, scarcely adaxially verrucose lip with angled margins 
<emphasis box="[649,672,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">vs</emphasis>
. oblong and conspicuously verrucose. From 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Lindl." baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[1192,1391,266,292]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="octomerioides">
<emphasis box="[1192,1391,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">M. octomerioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is distinguished by the yellowish whitish perianth 
<emphasis box="[675,698,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">vs</emphasis>
. perianth suffused with pink to purple. From 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1992" baseAuthorityName="Barb. Rodr." baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[1211,1366,302,328]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulvinatus">
<emphasis box="[1211,1366,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">M. pulvinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Soto Arenas" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="A. Rich. &amp; Galeotti" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="congestus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">M. congestus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it differs in the column with aciculate teeth on each side and acute to obtuse lip 
<emphasis box="[1175,1198,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">vs</emphasis>
. triangular, frequently bidentate on each side and generally apiculate lip.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[136,1452,158,617]" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">
When Soto Arenas revised Mexican 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Luer" authorityYear="1992" box="[615,752,410,436]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[615,752,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">Myoxanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, he noted that the original material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Richard &amp; Galeotti" authorityYear="1845" box="[1207,1338,411,436]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="congesta">
<emphasis box="[1207,1338,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">P. congesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fitted the concept of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Schlechter" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[262,426,447,472]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="octomeriae">
<emphasis box="[262,426,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">M. octomeriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
better than that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Lindl." baseAuthorityYear="1836" box="[641,838,446,472]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="octomerioides">
<emphasis box="[641,838,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">M. octomerioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as previously stated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Luer, C. A." box="[1111,1251,446,473]" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" pagination="34 - 54" refId="ref29456" refString="Luer, C. A. (1982 a) A reevaluation of the genus Myoxanthus (Orchidaceae). Selbyana 7: 34 - 54. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 14425" type="journal article" year="1982">
Luer (1982 
<bibRefCitation author="Luer, C. A." box="[1238,1251,446,472]" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" pagination="1 - 128" refId="ref29681" refString="Luer, C. A. (1992) Icones pleurothallidinarum IX. Systematic of Myoxanthus. Addenda to Platystele, Pleurothallis, subgenus Scopula and Scaphosepalum (Orchidaceae). Monographs in Systematic Botany, Missouri Botanical Garden 44: 1 - 128." type="journal article" year="1992">a</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, 1992; see Rojas- Alvarado &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Karremans, A. P. &amp; Vieira-Uribe, S." box="[282,471,482,509]" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" refId="ref28631" refString="Karremans, A. P. &amp; Vieira-Uribe, S. (2020) Pleurothallids Neotropical jewels, vol. 1. Mariscal, Quito, 311 pp." type="book" year="2020">Karremans 2020</bibRefCitation>
for an extended discussion). 
<emphasis box="[813,1107,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Garay &amp; Dunsterville" authorityYear="1976" box="[813,1103,482,508]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ramentacea">Pleurothallis ramentacea</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1298,1413,482,508]" name="Venezuela" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
by Garay &amp; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dunsterville, G. C. K. &amp; Garay, L. A." box="[237,457,518,545]" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" refId="ref28152" refString="Dunsterville, G. C. K. &amp; Garay, L. A. (1976) Venezuelan orchids illustrated, VI. Deutsch, London, 463 pp." type="book" year="1976">Dunsterville (1976)</bibRefCitation>
, also fits the concept of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Richard &amp; Galeotti" authorityYear="1845" box="[719,845,519,544]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="congesta">
<emphasis box="[719,845,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">P. congesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. See 
<emphasis box="[902,1056,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">Incertae sedis</emphasis>
at the end of this list of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1314,1451,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">Myoxanthus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
for a commentary of 
<taxonomicName authority="Klotzsch" authorityName="Klotzsch" box="[462,822,554,580]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Pleurothallis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis box="[462,713,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">Pleurothallis elongata</emphasis>
Klotzsch
</taxonomicName>
, which 
<bibRefCitation author="Rojas-Alvarado, G. &amp; Karremans, A. P." box="[910,1348,554,581]" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" pagination="1 - 70" refId="ref31437" refString="Rojas-Alvarado, G. &amp; Karremans, A. P. (2020) Revision of the Costa Rican species of Myoxanthus (Pleurothallidinae: Orchidaceae). Phytotaxa 448: 1 - 70. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 448.1.1" type="journal article" year="2020">Rojas-Alvarado and Karremans (2020)</bibRefCitation>
included as a synonym of 
<emphasis box="[326,481,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="235">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Soto Arenas" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="A. Rich. &amp; Galeotti" box="[326,477,591,616]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="24" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="congestus">M. congestus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
